ry happy to use it!',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(499,495,401,7,'This is the only one of the platform in theory: starts from doers to reach popular diffusion.',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(500,495,401,78,'You are referring to target. Platform TOV is: Multilocal. Inspiring, engaging, sometimes epic with never too much grandeur. Honest, positive and propositive.\r\n\r\nDo you think the video corresponds to it? \r\n\r\nI\'m not being \"teachy\"...I just want we start using brand heart and understanding how our strategy works and helps us. :)',1,1,1,0,1,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(501,495,401,7,'Thank you! I think it corresponds to multilocal, inspiring and propositive. But that\'s my point of view. It shows how kids have a cooperation-based thinking',1,0,1,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(502,428,401,22,'I agree that the it is controversial, I think articles like this one (related topic, strong point of view, famous person) might open some discussions in the page, making it more alive. Do we want to post only contents that \"we back up\" or also some contents to discuss about? For example on the money point, I saw it differently from Stela and it could lead to an interesting conversation :)',0,0,0,0,0,0,1,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(503,408,401,22,'You made me very interesting in knowing more about Tesla!! Thanks :)',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(504,495,401,107,'Ok, seeking perfection might be boring sometimes, and we cant always be perfect... but in the video I see a supercute kid playing with his father... innate tendency of family cooperation?? :))',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(505,491,401,107,'Kinda liked the anonymous one because of the guessing part/exercise I was having fun doing. \r\nSo, if you feel more comfortable this way, is ok for me. ',1,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(506,495,401,78,'don\'t get me wrong. I\'m not looking for perfection, but for consistency. I would avoid posting a video just because it\'s cute or has plenty of views. It should be consistent with our strategy. If it is so, as Alessandro discovered using our strategic tool, there is no reason not to include it in our editorial calendar. :-)',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(507,491,401,7,'The idea was to make a side button to set it anonymous or not :-)',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(508,495,401,7,'I must admit I am pretty more open to popular videos, just because I see in young guys the happiness of being playful. Young guys like videos like this A LOT: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=not1Yp4InUU&ab_channel=AleCfc',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(509,428,401,78,'Waiting for our FB official page to spread Cooperacy related contents (eg.: the platform projects, our webinars, educational messages about our governance etc.) we are looking for messages that might be consistent with our strategy, our vision and our mission. We have defined that our tone of voice shouldn\'t be provocative, or negative or controversial. We want to be inspiring, honest, propositive. What we need to ask ourselves is: is this message coherent with our aim? \r\nI have some doubts that this is appropriate for cooperacy.org FB account. I don\'t want cooperacy\'s messages might be misinterpreted due to a controversial article.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, I agree to bring some zest into our discussions...so maybe the appropriate audience for it is the cooperacy members\' page.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?',0,0,1,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(510,495,401,78,'ahahah. As Coomms Coordinator I think this is very funny but out of our strategy.\r\ncooperacy.org FB page, together with our website should be our \"official\" voice. it can work in members\' conversation to bring some \"mutual enjoyment\"...but would you talk to University or Institutional target that way?\r\n\r\nOr the moment we will target super narrowed messages to young guys, skaters, or whatever young community we can be more playful, in order to capture their attention. But I don\'t think this is the right approach at this stage.',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(511,495,401,78,'another option is ...we review the strategy. :-)',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(512,497,401,7,'I don\'t know I just think we should be multilocal. This means also risking a bit a speaking in different codes. I think you don\'t know the fenomenon.. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DROD5lqX8qo&ab_channel=BehindTheMeme there are tons of it, and the \"meme\" term was born by The Selfish Gene by Richard Dawkins... :D',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(513,497,401,7,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DROD5lqX8qo&ab_channel=BehindTheMeme\r\nWell I guess the meme phenomenon is quite big. That is what I meant with multilocal. It should address different codes and diversities. Meme is a term that comes from the scientific and divulgative book by Richard Dawkins \"The Selfish Gene\"..',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(514,495,401,7,'*** Comment deleted by author ***',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(515,495,401,7,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DROD5lqX8qo&ab_channel=BehindTheMeme\r\nwell the phenomenon is quite big! the idea behind the multilocal tov was that of joining different codes.. if you think that the word \"meme\" comes from the book The Selfish Gene by Richard Dawkins.. the sci community may be happy about it :D',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(516,495,401,78,'Different codes for different targets I agree, as previously mentioned. Or tailor made messages that the specific target can understand and embrace, I agree. \r\nYou might be surprised, but I know the phenomenon ;-)...this doesn\'t mean that a phenomenon can be always appropriate in all context. I make an example you might remember: at the time of the movie \"The Matrix\" everyone was using the bullet time effect in commercials...just because it was \"cool\"...not necessarily because it was the right approach to communication.\r\n\r\nIf there are cooperacy messages we can spread in a meme way, to an appropriate target, we will do it.',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(517,495,401,7,'So I guess the video is able to make people think in another way. There is a father and a son, but the son instead of a big clash like Luke Skywalker gives the colourful book to the father. That is a really strong moment in which people can understand another way of thinking.',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(518,495,401,78,'if you check the road map, the FB column, the video is already in plan for the first day of 2018.',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(519,0,401,22,'I had saved this one in my Fb, it\'s about the tragedy of the commons: https://www.facebook.com/TEDEducation/videos/1817323898280808/ \r\n\r\nI don\'t know what the introduction could be, probably Alessandro is the best person to think about one :)\r\n\r\nThe only \"flaw\" I see is that it doesn\'t mention Elinor :)',1,0,1,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-05-30 22:02:35'),(520,519,401,22,'I\'m trying to propose an intro: When the tragedy of the commons applies, whats good for all of us is good for each of us. It\'s the last sentence of the video',0,1,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(521,519,401,7,'That is very nice. ',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15','2019-04-25 23:54:54'),(522,519,401,7,'You can add, if you like, also a reference to Elinor, like \"We suggest the reading of Governing the Commons by Nobel Laureate Elinor Ostrom for who wants to learn more.\"',1,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2019-04-25 11:05:15',